{
  "texts": [
    "The (LSTM) architecture's adaptive gating mechanism enables it to capture and retain essential information over extended sequences, making it particularly well-suited for tasks involving temporal dynamics and sequential patterns.",
    "Moreover, the introduction of variants such as Bidirectional LSTM (BiLSTM) and Convolutional Neural Network -LSTM (CNN LSTM) has further extended the (LSTM) framework's capabilities, allowing for the exploitation of bidirectional context and spatial features, respectively.",
    "The Hyper-parameter tuning process determined that the model parameters and architecture comprise a single (LSTM) layer with 320 units.",
    "A learning rate of 0.000501 was identified as the most effective value for the learning process.",
    "To mitigate the problem of over-fitting, we introduced a dropout rate of 0.263337 and implemented an L2 regularizer."
  ]
}